RACE.RACE_TEXT: All Canadian Derby. CENTURY MILE RACE 1 300 Y Dirt CR: 74. Derby Purse 21200. A STAKES RACE FOR THREE YEAR OLD QUARTER HORSE WHICH QUALIFIED FOR THE FINALS. Weight 124lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PROFESSOR GEE gained the lead into the stretch and drove clear under confident handling. JAMEZ BOND lacked the rally needed and held. FDD FAST MAN stumbled leaving, and made a late run. NORTHFORK BOSS broke awkwardly, and rallied belatedly. APPRECIATE flattened late stretch. DECIDER CARTEL QUEEN bore out sharply away from the gate, and was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 2 350 Y Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TIMBER BUNNY vied for the early lead, dueled outside of SHAWNEE IS BOSS in the final yards and won the bob. SHAWNEE IS BOSS moved up alongside TIMBER BUNNY, was headed into the stretch, and lost the bob. BIG BOSS finished gamely for show. WESTERN BURNER vied four wide for the lead, and missed after a multi-horse scramble to the wire. DASHIN NORTH outsprinted leaving and lacked running room late. SLICK AS NICK GETS raced wide throughout and was outrun.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: Maiden Express Final CENTURY MILE RACE 3 350 Y Dirt CR: 74. Final Purse 27440. A FINAL FOR THREE YEAR OLD AND UPWARD QUARTER HORSES WHO QUALIFIED FOR THE MAIDEN EXPRESS FINAL. Weight: Three-Year-Olds: 124 lbs. Older: 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JUNK DRAWER reluctant to load and exploded late. TIMBERS MOON rallied inside and held on for place. FIRECRUNCH closed gradually and up in time. KARI L CARTEL rallied three wide, and was bested. MS CLARA stumbled hard leaving, and gained inside. INSEPERABLE COWGIRL raced evenly. NAUGHTEE OR NICE lacked clear run from the gate and finished well. HEZA MAJESTIC HERO lacked kick needed. EYEMADASHIN lacked serious bid.

LENT ME FIFTY chased the pace wide through the backstretch and faded.

GOLDEN FORTYNINE sat in striking distance while four wide through the backstretch, fanned four wide at the head of the lane, and yielded in drive. RACE.FOOTNOTES: KYSTONE allowed to settle early while three wide, roused at the head of the lane, and got up late under steady handling. LIFES ADVENTURE contested the pace outside of BARAK, lead the way through the final turn, and was out finished. BARAK contended the early pace from inside, steadied from between foes, and held on for show. SIX SHOTS OF T lodged a bid near the quarter pole, closed late and missed out. RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 15500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500. Alberta Bred Claiming Price $16,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TACOFLAVOREDKISSES raced near the back of the pack, closed huge and got by. COMMON KNOWLEDGE set the pace in the two path, responded to a challenge from SCHOCHOH and was caught late. SHARP DRESSED BEAU stalked the pacesetters, made a bid at the quarter pole and was outkicked in the final stages. SCHOCHOH sat just off the pace while five-wide, moved up alongside COMMON KNOWLEDGE at the head of the lane to challenge the lead, and lacked the closing response that needed. BARE BACK JACK made a late run improving his position in the stretch. TAPIT TO THE WIRE chased outside in the final turn, and passed tiring rival. EXPLODE showed good early speed from the rail, and gave way in the late stages. BANG ON was not a factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CENTURY MILE RACE 8 1M Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 10500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR ALBERTA BREDS WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $6,000 (Lesser Claim ing Races For $3,500 (AB $4,500) At Century Mile Not Considered In Eligibility). Alberta Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARSON'S LEGACY angled to the rail early then stalked the pacesetters, waited for running room in the final turn, circled into the lane, was given his cue, and won driving. DANZA UNBRIDLED went five-wide in the opening turn, sat in striking distance outside, went in pursuit of the leader, lugged in through the stretch and held for second. LITTLE CHICAGO returned to the paddock for a tack adjustment, rated just off the pace from between rivals, lodged a rail bid but lacked a clear path at the head of the stretch, and finished well outside. PULL THE PIN attended the pace from the three path, inherited the lead approaching the quarter pole, and flattened out inside. NEVVARE prompted the pace from between rivals, was unable to keep pace with the field and retreated. TRICKY SPEEDSTER went four to five-wide entering the opening turn, trailed through the backstretch, and lacked a serious bid. FLYING SUN chased outside and was outrun. HIGH KELLY SONG contested the pace from the rail under snug hold, and was done early.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bid inside, lacked clear path, finished well

RACE.FOOTNOTES: PADDYS ROCKET stalked outside through the backstretch, fanned three-wide into the far turn, drifted out, rallied determinedly outside of ROUGH CUSTOMER, and edged away. ROUGH CUSTOMER pressured the pace from an outside position, chased the leader into the final turn, dueled through the stretch and was bested after a long hard drive. PACHECO rated well off the early pacesetters, advanced inside quickly, and was outkicked. THE ITALIAN MAN chased inside, and weakened in the final furlong. BUSTER BRADY set a pressured pace, moved clear nearing the quarter pole, was overtaken, and yielded. OUR SUNSHINE saved ground and lacked a closing response when called upon. BIG JIM failed to threaten. COPPER MEIN was never involved.
